			<section class="comment-content comment">
				<p>The ironic thing is that the very fact that the United States is not an optimal cultural area is often brought up as a reason for why the United States is a  (morally?) optimal political area (or at least optimal relative to devolvement along cultural lines) &#8211; because we need to protect people in the South from the bad policies that they would democratically enact if devolution were to occur.</p>
							</section><!-- .comment-content -->

